snippet.textDisplay: As a cosplayer I understood this struggle so hard. Threading that damn machine is half the battle, and the other half is staying focused enough to actually sew straight. Cotton is the easiest to learn on as it's not super stretchy and is relatively easy to iron, which I would HIGHLY recommend to iron your fabrics during the process (gets those annoying wrinkles out!). Fyi, if you ever want a quick hem job for a nice finish just buy the iron-on hem tape for your clothes. Saves you the embarrassment if your stitches are as bad as mine. Keep it up, I think with practice you'll get better in no time! 😺
